      "**TL;DR:** The General Entertainment Authority (GEA) regulates all public entertainment events in Saudi Arabia. Events with live music, performances, or public access require a GEA permit. Processing takes 4–8 weeks. Key documents: event brief, venue confirmation, artist licenses, safety plan, and company commercial registration. Saudi Event Management handles GEA permits as a standard service.",
      "The General Entertainment Authority (GEA) was established in 2016 as part of Vision 2030 to regulate and grow Saudi Arabia's entertainment sector. Since its founding, the GEA has rapidly expanded the Kingdom's entertainment landscape — but with growth comes regulation. Any event featuring live performance, public entertainment, or amplified music in a public or semi-public setting requires GEA approval.",
      "## What Events Require a GEA Permit?",
      "GEA permits are required for: live music concerts and performances, comedy shows, theatrical productions, sports entertainment events, public festivals, cultural events with entertainment, corporate events with GEA-licensed performers, and Ramadan suhoor events with live entertainment. Private family gatherings at private residences generally do not require GEA permits.",
      "## Step-by-Step GEA Permit Process",
      "**Step 1 — Register on the GEA Portal:** Your company must be registered on the GEA Lichaat platform (lichaat.gea.gov.sa). You will need a valid Saudi commercial registration (CR) and Absher/Nafath authentication.",
      "**Step 2 — Prepare Your Application Documents:** Required documents include: detailed event brief (event type, date, time, location, expected attendance), signed venue contract, technical safety plan, artist/performer GEA licenses, security plan, and emergency evacuation plan.",
      "**Step 3 — Submit Your Application:** Submit through the GEA portal at least 4–8 weeks before your event date. High-profile events and those with international artists may require 10–12 weeks.",
      "**Step 4 — GEA Review and Site Inspection:** GEA will review your application and may conduct a site inspection. Be prepared to provide additional documentation or modify event plans based on their requirements.",
      "**Step 5 — Receive Your Permit:** Upon approval, you will receive your digital GEA permit which must be displayed at the event venue. Keep a copy for all senior production staff.",
      "## GEA Permit Costs",
      "GEA permit fees vary by event type and scale. Small corporate events: SAR 5,000–15,000. Large public concerts: SAR 50,000–250,000+. Fees are paid through the GEA portal and are non-refundable if the event is cancelled.",
      "## Most Common GEA Permit Mistakes",
      "1. Applying too late (less than 4 weeks before the event). 2. Incomplete documentation — especially missing artist GEA licenses. 3. Changing the event venue or date after permit approval without re-applying. 4. Failing to submit a proper security and crowd management plan.",
